{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862282773,"sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","part":{"id":"prt_d79a3f6b00017of4gvbzb0zs8w","messageID":"msg_d79a3df3d001mbeNqQLpGBypth","sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f68b735ee0be451e96bbbee5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-020\n10: - **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: The `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirements\n23: \n24: ### AR-020-001: Workspace validation\n25: \n26: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and contains valid agent source files based on the specified language.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-A — Valid Python workspace\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n31: - **WHEN** `pack` is executed with a Python agent (default language)\n32: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that at least one `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n33: - **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-B — Valid Java workspace\n36: \n37: - **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n38: - **WHEN** `pack` is executed with `--language java`\n39: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that `pom.xml` exists in the workspace root\n40: - **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-C — Missing workspace directory\n43: \n44: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist or is not a directory\n45: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n46: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-D — Python workspace without Python files\n49: \n50: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` resolves to `\"python\"` (default)\n51: - **WHEN** no `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n52: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-E — Java workspace without pom.xml\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"`\n57: - **WHEN** `pom.xml` does not exist in the workspace root\n58: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")`\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### AR-020-002: Metadata loading and merging\n63: \n64: The system SHALL load existing agent metadata from the workspace and merge CLI option overrides to create a complete metadata configuration.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-A — Load existing metadata\n67: \n68: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n69: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n70: - **THEN** the system SHALL load the metadata using `MetadataService.load_metadata`\n71: - **AND** return an `AgentMetadata` object with all fields populated\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-B — Fallback metadata file loading\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does NOT exist in the workspace\n76: - **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n77: - **THEN** the system SHALL attempt to load `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml` as fallbacks\n78: - **AND** raise `FileNotFoundError` if none of the fallback files exist\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-C — Create new metadata with defaults\n81: \n82: - **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n83: - **WHEN** `_load_or_create_metadata` runs\n84: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values:\n85:   - `language`: `\"python\"`\n86:   - `port`: `8080`\n87:   - `build_mode`: `\"local\"`\n88:   - `requirements_file`: `\"requirements.txt\"`\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-D — CLI option overrides\n91: \n92: - **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options are provided\n93: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` runs\n94: - **THEN** the system SHALL override metadata fields with CLI-provided values:\n95:   - `--agent-name` overrides `agent_name`\n96:   - `--language` overrides `language`\n97:   - `--entrypoint` overrides `entrypoint`\n98:   - `--port` overrides `port`\n99:   - `--build-mode` overrides `build_mode`\n100:   - `--description` overrides `description`\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### AR-020-003: Dockerfile generation\n105: \n106: The system SHALL generate a Dockerfile in the workspace when packaging Python or Java agents.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-A — Generate Python Dockerfile\n109: \n110: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n111: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n112: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_python_dockerfile`\n113: - **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Python base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-B — Generate Java Dockerfile\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n118: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n119: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n120: - **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Maven/Java base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-C — Skip Dockerfile when already exists\n123: \n124: - **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n125: - **WHEN** `_generate_dockerfile` runs\n126: - **THEN** the system SHALL NOT overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n127: - **AND** return `None` indicating no new Dockerfile was generated\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### AR-020-004: Dependency processing\n132: \n133: The system SHALL process agent dependencies based on the language.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-A — Process Python dependencies\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** `requirements.txt` exists in a Python workspace\n138: - **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n139: - **THEN** the system SHALL validate the requirements file format\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-B — Process Java dependencies\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** `pom.xml` exists in a Java workspace\n144: - **WHEN** `_process_java_dependencies` runs\n145: - **THEN** the system SHALL validate the POM file exists\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-C — Missing Python requirements file\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** workspace language is Python but `requirements.txt` does not exist\n150: - **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n151: - **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning but continue (requirements are optional)\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### AR-020-005: Output preparation\n156: \n157: The system SHALL prepare the output path for the packaged workspace.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-A — Default output path\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n162: - **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n163: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the original workspace path as the output\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-B — Custom output path\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** `--output` specifies a custom directory path\n168: - **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n169: - **THEN** the system SHALL create the output directory if it does not exist\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-C — Update metadata after packaging\n172: \n173: - **GIVEN** packaging completes successfully\n174: - **WHEN** `_update_pack_metadata` runs\n175: - **THEN** the system SHALL save the final `AgentMetadata` to `{output_path}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ### AR-020-006: CLI interface\n180: \n181: The system SHALL expose the `pack` command via Typer with specific options.\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-A — Pack command options\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack --help`\n186: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n187:   - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n188:   - `--agent-name NAME` — Override agent name\n189:   - `--language LANG` — Programming language (python, java)\n190:   - `--entrypoint CMD` — Override entrypoint command\n191:   - `--port PORT` — Port to expose (default: 8080)\n192:   - `--build-mode MODE` — Build strategy (local, cloud)\n193:   - `--description TEXT` — Agent description\n194:   - `--output PATH` — Output path for packaged workspace\n195:   - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-B — Successful pack output\n198: \n199: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace with all required files\n200: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n201: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success message using Rich `Progress` spinner\n202: - **AND** display agent name, resolved workspace path, and metadata file path\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-C — Pack failure with verbose logging\n205: \n206: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n207: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n208: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n209: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-D — Pack failure without verbose\n212: \n213: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n214: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n215: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red without traceback\n216: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ### AR-020-007: Language compatibility validation\n221: \n222: The system SHALL validate that the specified language and port are valid.\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-A — Valid language specification\n225: \n226: - **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n227: - **WHEN** `_validate_language_compatibility` runs\n228: - **THEN** the validation SHALL pass successfully\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-B — Invalid language specification\n231: \n232: - **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as an unsupported value\n233: - **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n234: - **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating valid options are `python` or `java`\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-C — Port range validation\n237: \n238: - **GIVEN** `--port` is provided with a value outside valid range\n239: - **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n240: - **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating port must be between 1 and 65535\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ### AR-020-008: Entrypoint inference\n245: \n246: The system SHALL infer the entrypoint command if not explicitly provided.\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: AR-020-008-A — Infer Python entrypoint\n249: \n250: - **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Python agent\n251: - **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n252: - **THEN** the system SHALL look for `main.py` in the workspace root\n253: - **AND** default to `python main.py` if found\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: AR-020-008-B — Infer Java entrypoint\n256: \n257: - **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Java agent\n258: - **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n259: - **THEN** the system SHALL look for a main class in `pom.xml`\n260: - **AND** default to `java -jar target/*.jar` if a JAR is expected\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ## Acceptance Criteria\n265: \n266: - [ ] AC001: Pack validates workspace structure before processing\n267: - [ ] AC002: Pack loads or creates metadata with proper defaults\n268: - [ ] AC003: Pack merges CLI option overrides into metadata\n269: - [ ] AC004: Pack generates Dockerfile when needed (Python/Java)\n270: - [ ] AC005: Pack processes dependencies for the target language\n271: - [ ] AC006: Pack prepares output path and saves metadata\n272: - [ ] AC007: Pack displays success output with Rich formatting\n273: - [ ] AC008: Pack handles errors with proper exit codes and verbose logging\n274: - [ ] AC009: Pack validates language and port values\n275: - [ ] AC010: Pack infers entrypoint when not provided\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ## Architecture Notes\n280: \n281: ### Key Components\n282: \n283: | Component | Path | Description |\n284: |-----------|------|-------------|\n285: | CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `pack` command |\n286: | PackRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packaging logic |\n287: | MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n288: | AgentMetadata | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Pydantic model for agent config |\n289: | DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Dockerfile generation and Docker operations |\n290: \n291: ### Metadata Fields (AgentMetadata)\n292: \n293: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n294: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n295: | agent_name | str | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n296: | language | str | \"python\" | Programming language used |\n297: | entrypoint | str | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n298: | port | int | 8080 | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n299: | build_mode | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n300: | description | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n301: | requirements_file | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | Python dependency file |\n302: \n303: ### CLI Options Mapping\n304: \n305: | CLI Option | Metadata Field | Type |\n306: |------------|----------------|------|\n307: | `--agent-name` | agent_name | Optional[str] |\n308: | `--language` | language | Optional[str] |\n309: | `--entrypoint` | entrypoint | Optional[str] |\n310: | `--port` | port | Optional[int] |\n311: | `--build-mode` | build_mode | Optional[str] |\n312: | `--description` | description | Optional[str] |\n313: | `--output` | (output path) | Optional[str] |\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ## References\n318: \n319: - Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n320: - Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n321: - CLI entry point: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n322: - Runtime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n323: - Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n324: - Docker service: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n\n(End of file - total 324 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-020\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775862282763,"end":1775862282771}}}}
