{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862297935,"sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","part":{"id":"prt_d79a4317d001HN0Xs9nVLWbPOt","messageID":"msg_d79a426e70015YMsAYpNdQbmON","sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7f748a6b9fec41d9bb750161","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI publish command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-022\n10: - **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: L\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: (TODO: Describe the publish command purpose and workflow)\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirements\n23: \n24: ### AR-022-001: CLI interface\n25: \n26: The system SHALL expose the `publish` command via Typer with specific options.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-022-001-A — Publish command options\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --help`\n31: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n32:   - (TODO: Define CLI options)\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: AR-022-001-B — Default options\n35: \n36: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish` with no options\n37: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be applied:\n38:   - (TODO: Define defaults)\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ### AR-022-002: Publish prerequisites validation\n43: \n44: The system SHALL validate publish prerequisites before proceeding.\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: AR-022-002-A — Validate workspace exists\n47: \n48: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n49: - **WHEN** validation runs\n50: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: AR-022-002-B — Validate metadata exists\n53: \n54: - **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain `agent_metadata.yaml`\n55: - **WHEN** publish runs\n56: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: AR-022-002-C — Validate image exists\n59: \n60: - **GIVEN** required container image does not exist\n61: - **WHEN** publish runs\n62: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `RuntimeError`\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ### AR-022-003: Registry publish\n67: \n68: The system SHALL publish the container image to a container registry.\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: AR-022-003-A — Publish to registry\n71: \n72: - **GIVEN** valid image and registry configuration\n73: - **WHEN** publish runs\n74: - **THEN** the system SHALL push the image to the registry\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: AR-022-003-B — Publish with custom registry\n77: \n78: - **GIVEN** `--registry` option is provided\n79: - **WHEN** publish runs\n80: - **THEN** the system SHALL push to the specified registry\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: AR-022-003-C — Publish with authentication\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** registry credentials are configured\n85: - **WHEN** publish runs\n86: - **THEN** the system SHALL authenticate before pushing\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: AR-022-003-D — Publish failure handling\n89: \n90: - **GIVEN** registry push fails\n91: - **WHEN** publish runs\n92: - **THEN** the system SHALL propagate the error\n93: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ### AR-022-004: Registry authentication\n98: \n99: The system SHALL handle registry authentication securely.\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: AR-022-004-A — Use configured credentials\n102: \n103: - **GIVEN** credentials are configured in config file\n104: - **WHEN** publish runs\n105: - **THEN** the system SHALL use those credentials\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: AR-022-004-B — Login on demand\n108: \n109: - **GIVEN** `--login` option is provided\n110: - **WHEN** publish runs\n111: - **THEN** the system SHALL perform registry login first\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ### AR-022-005: Version handling\n116: \n117: The system SHALL handle version information during publish.\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: AR-022-005-A — Use version from metadata\n120: \n121: - **GIVEN** metadata contains version\n122: - **WHEN** publish runs\n123: - **THEN** the system SHALL tag image with that version\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: AR-022-005-B — Custom tag\n126: \n127: - **GIVEN** `--tag` option is provided\n128: - **WHEN** publish runs\n129: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom tag\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ### AR-022-006: Publish metadata update\n134: \n135: The system SHALL update workspace metadata with publish results.\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: AR-022-006-A — Update metadata after publish\n138: \n139: - **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n140: - **WHEN** metadata is updated\n141: - **THEN** the system SHALL save registry URL and publish timestamp\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ### AR-022-007: Error handling\n146: \n147: The system SHALL handle errors with appropriate error messages and exit codes.\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: AR-022-007-A — Publish error with verbose logging\n150: \n151: - **GIVEN** publish raises an exception\n152: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n153: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message with full traceback\n154: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: AR-022-007-B — Publish error without verbose\n157: \n158: - **GIVEN** publish raises an exception\n159: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n160: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message without traceback\n161: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ### AR-022-008: Successful publish output\n166: \n167: The system SHALL display success messages with publish details.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: AR-022-008-A — Display publish success\n170: \n171: - **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n172: - **WHEN** the command finishes\n173: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display success message with:\n174:   - Registry URL\n175:   - Image full name\n176:   - Publish timestamp\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ## Acceptance Criteria\n181: \n182: - [ ] AC001: Publish command accepts all specified CLI options\n183: - [ ] AC002: Publish validates workspace and metadata exist before proceeding\n184: - [ ] AC003: Publish validates image exists before pushing\n185: - [ ] AC004: Publish pushes image to specified registry\n186: - [ ] AC005: Publish handles registry authentication\n187: - [ ] AC006: Publish uses version from metadata or custom tag\n188: - [ ] AC007: Publish metadata is updated with registry information\n189: - [ ] AC008: Publish displays success output with Rich formatting\n190: - [ ] AC009: Publish handles errors with appropriate exit codes and verbose logging\n191: \n192: ---\n193: \n194: ## Architecture Notes\n195: \n196: ### Key Components\n197: \n198: | Component | Path | Description |\n199: |-----------|------|-------------|\n200: | CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `publish` command |\n201: | PublishRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Core publish logic |\n202: | RegistryService | `agentcube/services/registry_service.py` | Registry operations |\n203: | DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Docker SDK operations |\n204: | MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n205: \n206: ### Publish Flow\n207: \n208: ```\n209: publish command\n210:     └─> PublishRuntime.publish()\n211:             ├─> _validate_publish_prerequisites()\n212:             ├─> _authenticate_registry()\n213:             ├─> _push_to_registry()\n214:             └─> _update_publish_metadata()\n215: ```\n216: \n217: ### CLI Options Mapping\n218: \n219: | CLI Option | Runtime Parameter | Type |\n220: |------------|-------------------|------|\n221: | `-f, --workspace` | workspace_path | str |\n222: | `-r, --registry` | options[\"registry\"] | Optional[str] |\n223: | `-t, --tag` | options[\"tag\"] | Optional[str] |\n224: | `--login` | options[\"login\"] | bool |\n225: | `--verbose` | verbose | bool |\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ## References\n230: \n231: - Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n232: - Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n233: - CLI entry point: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n234: - Runtime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n235: - Registry service: `agentcube/services/registry_service.py`\n236: - Docker service: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n237: - Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n238: - Related: AR-021 (build command)\n\n(End of file - total 238 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI publish command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-022\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\n(TODO: Describe the publish command purpose and workflow)\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775862297918,"end":1775862297932}}}}
