{"type":"text","timestamp":1775862304253,"sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","part":{"id":"prt_d79a44be3001dQceSqts4NfW25","messageID":"msg_d79a4357b001fHXpaDbw50MB9I","sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","type":"text","text":"The existing AR-022 delta-spec.md has incorrect content (TODOs and wrong implementation details). I'll rewrite it to match the actual base specs.","time":{"start":1775862304251,"end":1775862304251}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862348092,"sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","part":{"id":"prt_d79a44dfd001Nu8AiUGgds2Wcj","messageID":"msg_d79a4357b001fHXpaDbw50MB9I","sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_a55f42efd21b465dbaa10962","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI publish command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-022\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `publish` command is the final step in the AgentCube workflow. It deploys the packaged agent to either AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or standard Kubernetes (Deployment + Service). The command prepares the container image, handles registry authentication, creates the appropriate Kubernetes resources, and updates metadata with deployment information.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-022-001: CLI interface\n\nThe system SHALL expose the `publish` command via Typer with specific options.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-001-A — Publish command options\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --help`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n  - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n  - `--version VERSION` — Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\n  - `--image-url URL` — Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\n  - `--image-username USER` — Username for image repository\n  - `--image-password PASS` — Password for image repository\n  - `--description TEXT` — Agent description\n  - `--region REGION` — Deployment region\n  - `--cloud-provider PROVIDER` — Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n  - `--provider PROVIDER` — Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' (default: \"agentcube\")\n  - `--node-port PORT` — Specific NodePort (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\n  - `--replicas COUNT` — Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\n  - `--namespace NAMESPACE` — The namespace for the deployment\n  - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-001-B — Default options\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish` with no options\n- **THEN** defaults SHALL be applied:\n  - `workspace`: `\".\"`\n  - `provider`: `\"agentcube\"`\n  - `verbose`: `False`\n  - All other options: `None`\n\n---\n\n### AR-022-002: Publish prerequisites validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate publish prerequisites before proceeding.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-002-A — Validate workspace exists\n\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** publish runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-002-B — Validate metadata exists\n\n- **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **WHEN** publish runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-002-C — AgentCube provider prerequisites\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"`\n- **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n---\n\n### AR-022-003: Image preparation\n\nThe system SHALL prepare the container image for publishing.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-003-A — Prepare local image\n\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` in metadata is `\"local\"`\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the locally built image from metadata\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-003-B — Prepare cloud image\n\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` in metadata is `\"cloud\"`\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_cloud_image` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the cloud registry image URL\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-003-C — Image push to registry\n\n- **GIVEN** valid image and registry credentials (`--image-username`, `--image-password`)\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_image_for_publishing` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL push the image to the registry\n- **AND** return the pushed image URL\n\n---\n\n### AR-022-004: AgentCube provider deployment\n\nThe system SHALL create an AgentRuntime CR for AgentCube deployments.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-004-A — Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` and all prerequisites are met\n- **WHEN** `_publish_cr_to_k8s` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime`\n- **AND** the CR SHALL be created in namespace from `--namespace` or \"default\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-004-B — CR environment variables\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n- **WHEN** creating the AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** the system SHALL embed `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` from metadata parameters or environment\n- **AND** set `sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"`\n- **AND** set `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`\n- **AND** reference `imagePullSecrets` as `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-004-C — CR status update\n\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is deployed successfully\n- **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL save `agent_id`, deployment info to metadata\n\n---\n\n### AR-022-005: Kubernetes provider deployment\n\nThe system SHALL create Deployment and NodePort Service for standard Kubernetes deployments.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-005-A — Deploy to K8s\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"` and Kubernetes client initializes\n- **WHEN** `_publish_k8s` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`\n- **AND** create a Deployment with specified `replicas`\n- **AND** create a NodePort Service with specified `node_port` or auto-assigned port\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-005-B — Wait for deployment ready\n\n- **GIVEN** a K8s deployment is created\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL wait up to 120 seconds for pods to be ready\n- **AND** raise `TimeoutError` if timeout is exceeded\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-005-C — K8s deployment metadata update\n\n- **GIVEN** K8s deployment completes successfully\n- **WHEN** metadata is updated\n- **THEN** the system SHALL save `k8s_deployment` with:\n  - `deployment_name`\n  - `service_name`\n  - `namespace`\n  - `replicas`\n  - `container_port`\n  - `node_port`\n  - `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n\n---\n\n### AR-022-006: Version handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle version information during publish.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-006-A — Use version from CLI option\n\n- **GIVEN** `--version` option is provided (e.g., \"v1.0.0\")\n- **WHEN** publish runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use that version for image tagging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-006-B — Use version from metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** `--version` is not provided\n- **WHEN** publish runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use version from `metadata.version`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-006-C — Default version\n\n- **GIVEN** neither CLI nor metadata provides version\n- **WHEN** publish runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `\"latest\"` as default tag\n\n---\n\n### AR-022-007: Error handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle errors with appropriate error messages and exit codes.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-007-A — Publish error with verbose logging\n\n- **GIVEN** publish raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-007-B — Publish error without verbose\n\n- **GIVEN** publish raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red without traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-007-C — K8s readiness timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** K8s deployment pods do not become ready within 120 seconds\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `TimeoutError`\n- **AND** record error in metadata\n\n---\n\n### AR-022-008: Successful publish output\n\nThe system SHALL display success messages with publish details.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-022-008-A — Display publish success\n\n- **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n- **WHEN** the command finishes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display success message with:\n  - Agent name\n  - Provider type (agentcube/k8s)\n  - Deployment namespace\n  - Service URL (for K8s) or AgentRuntime info (for AgentCube)\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: Publish command accepts all specified CLI options\n- [ ] AC002: Publish validates workspace and metadata exist before proceeding\n- [ ] AC003: Publish validates AgentCube prerequisites (router_url, workload_manager_url)\n- [ ] AC004: Publish prepares image for registry (local or cloud mode)\n- [ ] AC005: Publish deploys AgentRuntime CR when provider is \"agentcube\"\n- [ ] AC006: Publish deploys K8s Deployment/Service when provider is \"k8s\"\n- [ ] AC007: Publish waits for K8s deployment readiness (timeout: 120s)\n- [ ] AC008: Publish handles version from CLI, metadata, or default \"latest\"\n- [ ] AC009: Publish updates metadata with deployment information\n- [ ] AC010: Publish displays success output with Rich formatting\n- [ ] AC011: Publish handles errors with appropriate exit codes and verbose logging\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `publish` command |\n| PublishRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Core publish logic |\n| AgentCubeProvider | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR operations |\n| KubernetesProvider | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | K8s Deployment/Service operations |\n| DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Docker SDK operations |\n| MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n\n### Publish Flow\n\n```\npublish command (provider=agentcube)\n    └─> PublishRuntime.publish()\n            ├─> _prepare_image_for_publishing()\n            │       └─> _prepare_local_image() / _prepare_cloud_image()\n            └─> _publish_cr_to_k8s()\n                    └─> AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()\n\npublish command (provider=k8s)\n    └─> PublishRuntime.publish()\n            ├─> _prepare_image_for_publishing()\n            └─> _publish_k8s()\n                    ├─> KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()\n                    └─> wait_for_deployment_ready(timeout=120)\n```\n\n### CLI Options Mapping\n\n| CLI Option | Runtime Parameter | Type |\n|------------|-------------------|------|\n| `-f, --workspace` | workspace_path | str |\n| `--version` | options[\"version\"] | Optional[str] |\n| `--image-url` | options[\"image_url\"] | Optional[str] |\n| `--image-username` | options[\"image_username\"] | Optional[str] |\n| `--image-password` | options[\"image_password\"] | Optional[str] |\n| `--description` | options[\"description\"] | Optional[str] |\n| `--region` | options[\"region\"] | Optional[str] |\n| `--cloud-provider` | options[\"cloud_provider\"] | Optional[str] |\n| `--provider` | provider | str (default: \"agentcube\") |\n| `--node-port` | options[\"node_port\"] | Optional[int] |\n| `--replicas` | options[\"replicas\"] | Optional[int] |\n| `--namespace` | options[\"namespace\"] | Optional[str] |\n| `--verbose` | verbose | bool |\n\n### Provider Types\n\n| Provider | Kubernetes Resource | Description |\n|----------|---------------------|-------------|\n| `agentcube` | AgentRuntime CR (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1) | AgentCube custom resource |\n| `k8s` | Deployment + NodePort Service | Standard Kubernetes resources |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n- Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n- CLI entry point: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n- Runtime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n- AgentCube provider: `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n- Kubernetes provider: `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n- Docker service: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n- Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- Related: AR-020 (pack command), AR-021 (build command)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775862348061,"end":1775862348089}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775862348118,"sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","part":{"id":"prt_d79a4f93b001SrJ16tLdGc2N14","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79a4357b001fHXpaDbw50MB9I","sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":46950,"input":2412,"output":3196,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":41342}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775862350171,"sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","part":{"id":"prt_d79a50158001BDWZ1J4lVbcHeG","messageID":"msg_d79a4f96c001ITEdvf3bTGUpyL","sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862357319,"sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","part":{"id":"prt_d79a518f70011EVu6gxCE76O0V","messageID":"msg_d79a4f96c001ITEdvf3bTGUpyL","sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ce5d7b8ab15c4e3bab0ab03f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI publish command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-022\n10: - **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: L\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: The `publish` command is the final step in the AgentCube workflow. It deploys the packaged agent to either AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or standard Kubernetes (Deployment + Service). The command prepares the container image, handles registry authentication, creates the appropriate Kubernetes resources, and updates metadata with deployment information.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirements\n23: \n24: ### AR-022-001: CLI interface\n25: \n26: The system SHALL expose the `publish` command via Typer with specific options.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-022-001-A — Publish command options\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --help`\n31: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n32:   - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n33:   - `--version VERSION` — Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\n34:   - `--image-url URL` — Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\n35:   - `--image-username USER` — Username for image repository\n36:   - `--image-password PASS` — Password for image repository\n37:   - `--description TEXT` — Agent description\n38:   - `--region REGION` — Deployment region\n39:   - `--cloud-provider PROVIDER` — Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n40:   - `--provider PROVIDER` — Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' (default: \"agentcube\")\n41:   - `--node-port PORT` — Specific NodePort (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\n42:   - `--replicas COUNT` — Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\n43:   - `--namespace NAMESPACE` — The namespace for the deployment\n44:   - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: AR-022-001-B — Default options\n47: \n48: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish` with no options\n49: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be applied:\n50:   - `workspace`: `\".\"`\n51:   - `provider`: `\"agentcube\"`\n52:   - `verbose`: `False`\n53:   - All other options: `None`\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### AR-022-002: Publish prerequisites validation\n58: \n59: The system SHALL validate publish prerequisites before proceeding.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: AR-022-002-A — Validate workspace exists\n62: \n63: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n64: - **WHEN** publish runs\n65: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: AR-022-002-B — Validate metadata exists\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain `agent_metadata.yaml`\n70: - **WHEN** publish runs\n71: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: AR-022-002-C — AgentCube provider prerequisites\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"`\n76: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n77: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ### AR-022-003: Image preparation\n82: \n83: The system SHALL prepare the container image for publishing.\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: AR-022-003-A — Prepare local image\n86: \n87: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` in metadata is `\"local\"`\n88: - **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image` runs\n89: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the locally built image from metadata\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: AR-022-003-B — Prepare cloud image\n92: \n93: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` in metadata is `\"cloud\"`\n94: - **WHEN** `_prepare_cloud_image` runs\n95: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the cloud registry image URL\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: AR-022-003-C — Image push to registry\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** valid image and registry credentials (`--image-username`, `--image-password`)\n100: - **WHEN** `_prepare_image_for_publishing` runs\n101: - **THEN** the system SHALL push the image to the registry\n102: - **AND** return the pushed image URL\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ### AR-022-004: AgentCube provider deployment\n107: \n108: The system SHALL create an AgentRuntime CR for AgentCube deployments.\n109: \n110: #### Scenario: AR-022-004-A — Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n111: \n112: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` and all prerequisites are met\n113: - **WHEN** `_publish_cr_to_k8s` runs\n114: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime`\n115: - **AND** the CR SHALL be created in namespace from `--namespace` or \"default\"\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: AR-022-004-B — CR environment variables\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n120: - **WHEN** creating the AgentRuntime\n121: - **THEN** the system SHALL embed `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` from metadata parameters or environment\n122: - **AND** set `sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"`\n123: - **AND** set `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`\n124: - **AND** reference `imagePullSecrets` as `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: AR-022-004-C — CR status update\n127: \n128: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is deployed successfully\n129: - **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata` runs\n130: - **THEN** the system SHALL save `agent_id`, deployment info to metadata\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ### AR-022-005: Kubernetes provider deployment\n135: \n136: The system SHALL create Deployment and NodePort Service for standard Kubernetes deployments.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: AR-022-005-A — Deploy to K8s\n139: \n140: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"` and Kubernetes client initializes\n141: - **WHEN** `_publish_k8s` runs\n142: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`\n143: - **AND** create a Deployment with specified `replicas`\n144: - **AND** create a NodePort Service with specified `node_port` or auto-assigned port\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: AR-022-005-B — Wait for deployment ready\n147: \n148: - **GIVEN** a K8s deployment is created\n149: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` runs\n150: - **THEN** the system SHALL wait up to 120 seconds for pods to be ready\n151: - **AND** raise `TimeoutError` if timeout is exceeded\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: AR-022-005-C — K8s deployment metadata update\n154: \n155: - **GIVEN** K8s deployment completes successfully\n156: - **WHEN** metadata is updated\n157: - **THEN** the system SHALL save `k8s_deployment` with:\n158:   - `deployment_name`\n159:   - `service_name`\n160:   - `namespace`\n161:   - `replicas`\n162:   - `container_port`\n163:   - `node_port`\n164:   - `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ### AR-022-006: Version handling\n169: \n170: The system SHALL handle version information during publish.\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: AR-022-006-A — Use version from CLI option\n173: \n174: - **GIVEN** `--version` option is provided (e.g., \"v1.0.0\")\n175: - **WHEN** publish runs\n176: - **THEN** the system SHALL use that version for image tagging\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: AR-022-006-B — Use version from metadata\n179: \n180: - **GIVEN** `--version` is not provided\n181: - **WHEN** publish runs\n182: - **THEN** the system SHALL use version from `metadata.version`\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: AR-022-006-C — Default version\n185: \n186: - **GIVEN** neither CLI nor metadata provides version\n187: - **WHEN** publish runs\n188: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `\"latest\"` as default tag\n189: \n190: ---\n191: \n192: ### AR-022-007: Error handling\n193: \n194: The system SHALL handle errors with appropriate error messages and exit codes.\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: AR-022-007-A — Publish error with verbose logging\n197: \n198: - **GIVEN** publish raises an exception\n199: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n200: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n201: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: AR-022-007-B — Publish error without verbose\n204: \n205: - **GIVEN** publish raises an exception\n206: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n207: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red without traceback\n208: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: AR-022-007-C — K8s readiness timeout\n211: \n212: - **GIVEN** K8s deployment pods do not become ready within 120 seconds\n213: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` runs\n214: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `TimeoutError`\n215: - **AND** record error in metadata\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ### AR-022-008: Successful publish output\n220: \n221: The system SHALL display success messages with publish details.\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: AR-022-008-A — Display publish success\n224: \n225: - **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n226: - **WHEN** the command finishes\n227: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display success message with:\n228:   - Agent name\n229:   - Provider type (agentcube/k8s)\n230:   - Deployment namespace\n231:   - Service URL (for K8s) or AgentRuntime info (for AgentCube)\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: ## Acceptance Criteria\n236: \n237: - [ ] AC001: Publish command accepts all specified CLI options\n238: - [ ] AC002: Publish validates workspace and metadata exist before proceeding\n239: - [ ] AC003: Publish validates AgentCube prerequisites (router_url, workload_manager_url)\n240: - [ ] AC004: Publish prepares image for registry (local or cloud mode)\n241: - [ ] AC005: Publish deploys AgentRuntime CR when provider is \"agentcube\"\n242: - [ ] AC006: Publish deploys K8s Deployment/Service when provider is \"k8s\"\n243: - [ ] AC007: Publish waits for K8s deployment readiness (timeout: 120s)\n244: - [ ] AC008: Publish handles version from CLI, metadata, or default \"latest\"\n245: - [ ] AC009: Publish updates metadata with deployment information\n246: - [ ] AC010: Publish displays success output with Rich formatting\n247: - [ ] AC011: Publish handles errors with appropriate exit codes and verbose logging\n248: \n249: ---\n250: \n251: ## Architecture Notes\n252: \n253: ### Key Components\n254: \n255: | Component | Path | Description |\n256: |-----------|------|-------------|\n257: | CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `publish` command |\n258: | PublishRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Core publish logic |\n259: | AgentCubeProvider | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR operations |\n260: | KubernetesProvider | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | K8s Deployment/Service operations |\n261: | DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Docker SDK operations |\n262: | MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n263: \n264: ### Publish Flow\n265: \n266: ```\n267: publish command (provider=agentcube)\n268:     └─> PublishRuntime.publish()\n269:             ├─> _prepare_image_for_publishing()\n270:             │       └─> _prepare_local_image() / _prepare_cloud_image()\n271:             └─> _publish_cr_to_k8s()\n272:                     └─> AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()\n273: \n274: publish command (provider=k8s)\n275:     └─> PublishRuntime.publish()\n276:             ├─> _prepare_image_for_publishing()\n277:             └─> _publish_k8s()\n278:                     ├─> KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()\n279:                     └─> wait_for_deployment_ready(timeout=120)\n280: ```\n281: \n282: ### CLI Options Mapping\n283: \n284: | CLI Option | Runtime Parameter | Type |\n285: |------------|-------------------|------|\n286: | `-f, --workspace` | workspace_path | str |\n287: | `--version` | options[\"version\"] | Optional[str] |\n288: | `--image-url` | options[\"image_url\"] | Optional[str] |\n289: | `--image-username` | options[\"image_username\"] | Optional[str] |\n290: | `--image-password` | options[\"image_password\"] | Optional[str] |\n291: | `--description` | options[\"description\"] | Optional[str] |\n292: | `--region` | options[\"region\"] | Optional[str] |\n293: | `--cloud-provider` | options[\"cloud_provider\"] | Optional[str] |\n294: | `--provider` | provider | str (default: \"agentcube\") |\n295: | `--node-port` | options[\"node_port\"] | Optional[int] |\n296: | `--replicas` | options[\"replicas\"] | Optional[int] |\n297: | `--namespace` | options[\"namespace\"] | Optional[str] |\n298: | `--verbose` | verbose | bool |\n299: \n300: ### Provider Types\n301: \n302: | Provider | Kubernetes Resource | Description |\n303: |----------|---------------------|-------------|\n304: | `agentcube` | AgentRuntime CR (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1) | AgentCube custom resource |\n305: | `k8s` | Deployment + NodePort Service | Standard Kubernetes resources |\n306: \n307: ---\n308: \n309: ## References\n310: \n311: - Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n312: - Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n313: - CLI entry point: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n314: - Runtime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n315: - AgentCube provider: `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n316: - Kubernetes provider: `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n317: - Docker service: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n318: - Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n319: - Related: AR-020 (pack command), AR-021 (build command)\n\n(End of file - total 319 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI publish command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-022\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `publish` command is the final step in the AgentCube workflow. It deploys the packaged agent to either AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or standard Kubernetes (Deployment + Service). The command prepares the container image, handles registry authentication, creates the appropriate Kubernetes resources, and updates metadata with deployment information.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775862357300,"end":1775862357316}}}}
