{"type":"text","timestamp":1775862364051,"sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","part":{"id":"prt_d79a52d3f001m37Xe715v0FaZZ","messageID":"msg_d79a51d75001XSzmFLQr3Ap9IJ","sessionID":"ses_2865c564cffex78Y8jQhDZm9bX","type":"text","text":"Done. The `changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md` has been updated with complete GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios for the CLI publish command, covering:\n\n- CLI interface with all 13 options (workspace, version, image-url, credentials, provider, node-port, replicas, namespace, etc.)\n- Prerequisites validation (workspace, metadata, AgentCube router_url/workload_manager_url)\n- Image preparation (local/cloud build modes, registry push)\n- AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR deployment)\n- Kubernetes provider (Deployment + NodePort Service with 120s readiness timeout)\n- Version handling (CLI, metadata, or default \"latest\")\n- Error handling with verbose/non-verbose modes\n- Success output formatting\n\nThe spec aligns with the actual `PublishRuntime`, `AgentCubeProvider`, and `KubernetesProvider` implementation from the base specs.","time":{"start":1775862364049,"end":1775862364049}}}
